description.narrative: Capacity of services providers to provide quality and integrated health, HIV, nutrition, education, sanitation, birth registration and child protection services improved, which contributes to Access To Justice, Child Health, Child Poverty / Public Finance For Children, Children With Disabilities, Early Childhood Development, Equitable Access To Quality Education, Equitable Access To Quality Education (Covid), Gender Discriminatory Roles And Practices, Hiv Prevention, Immunization, Learning Outcomes, Maternal And Newborn Health, Maternal And Newborn Health (Covid), Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Sanitation, Supply And Logistics, Treatment And Care Of Children Living With Hiv, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition (Covid), Water. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: All Namibian children from ages 0â€“10 years have improved access to quality and equitable maternal, neonatal and child health, education, child protection, ECD, civil registration, nutrition and WASH services by 2023.

title.narrative: Capacity of services providers to provide quality and integrated health, HIV, nutrition, education, sanitation, birth registration and child protection services improved

description.narrative: In 2019, 1187 service providers of critical interventions in Health, Nutrition, WASH, eMTCT of HIV, Birth Registration, and ECD were capacitated to provide quality services through targeted trainings. Information systems were strengthened, and life-saving supplies and commodities provided to manage acute malnutrition and improve newborn health outcomes in five regions. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:11/12/2019

title.narrative: Country routinely collects and publishes key types of administrative data on violence, exploitation and abuse of children, disaggregated by age and sex
Number of healthcare facility staff and community health workers (TRAINED IN INFECTION PREVENTION AND CONTROL (IPC))

Status of development of integrated e-information systems for health, education and IECD linked to e-NPRS
Number of children and women receiving (ESSENTIAL HEALTHCARE SERVICES) in UNICEF supported facilities
Share of the national budget on health

Percentage of stock out of essential vaccine supplies
Percentage of justice professionals that have been certified in and dealing with: (a) child offenders; and (b) child victims
Percentage of districts implementing at least 3 interventions to improve the quality of maternal and newborn care at primary health care level
Percentage of UNICEF supported health facilities offering delivery services with functional newborn resuscitation equipment (functional bag and mask in neonatal size)

Number of Civil Registrars or other cadres (i.e. health workers, community leaders, teachers act.) who are legally mandated to notify or register births and who have received training on birth notification or registration
Percentage of schools with sanitation and hygiene facilities separated for girls and boys and that meet national standards
